Title: User Access Review Procedure and Evidence

Purpose
Kahana performs periodic user access reviews for all in‑scope systems to ensure access is appropriate and based on least privilege.

Process

Scope: Production infrastructure, application admin consoles, source code repositories, corporate SaaS (IdP, ticketing, finance tools).

Frequency: Quarterly.

Steps:

Export current user and role listings from each in‑scope system.

Send to the designated system owner for review and sign‑off.

Remove or adjust any inappropriate, stale, or excessive access.

Store approved reviews and remediation tickets in <folder/tool>.

Evidence kept for Type II:

Review exports, annotated with “keep/remove/change” decisions.

Approvals (email, ticket comments, or sign‑off in GDrive/Notion).

Tickets showing deprovisioning or privilege reductions.